</HEAD><BODY BACKGROUND='Image1.jpg'><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Sacred Name King James    
Version</H3><P><A HREF='B01C020.htm'>Genesis 20</A></P><CENTER><H2 ALIGN=CENTER>
The First Book of Moses, called Genesis</H2></CENTER><P><A HREF='index.htm'>    
Return to Index</A>.</P><CENTER><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=5 WIDTH=90%><TR><TD>
</TD><TD><CENTER><H1>Chapter 21</H1></CENTER></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A    
NAME=V1><H4>1</H4></TD><TD><P>And YHVH visited Sarah as he had said, and YHVH   
did unto Sarah as he had spoken.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V2><H4>
2</H4></TD><TD><P>For Sarah conceived, and bare Abraham a son in his old age,   
at the set time of which ELOHIYM had spoken to him.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD        
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V3><H4>3</H4></TD><TD><P>And Abraham called the name of his  
son that was born unto him, whom Sarah bare to him, Isaac.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD 
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V4><H4>4</H4></TD><TD><P>And Abraham circumcised his son     
Isaac being eight days old, as ELOHIYM had commanded him.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD  
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V5><H4>5</H4></TD><TD><P>And Abraham was an hundred years    
old, when his son Isaac was born unto him.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A   
NAME=V6><H4>6</H4></TD><TD><P>And Sarah said, ELOHIYM hath made me to laugh, so 
that all that hear will laugh with me.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A       
NAME=V7><H4>7</H4></TD><TD><P>And she said, Who would have said unto Abraham,   
that Sarah should have given children suck? for I have born him a son in his    
old age.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V8><H4>8</H4></TD><TD><P>And   
the child grew, and was weaned: and Abraham made a great feast the same day     
that Isaac was weaned.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V9><H4>9</H4>    
</TD><TD><P>And Sarah saw the son of Hagar the Egyptian, which she had born     
unto Abraham, mocking.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V10><H4>10</H4>  
</TD><TD><P>Wherefore she said unto Abraham, Cast out this bondwoman and her    
son: for the son of this bondwoman shall not be heir with my son, even with     
Isaac.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V11><H4>11</H4></TD><TD><P>And   
the thing was very grievous in Abraham's sight because of his son.</P></TD></TR>
<TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V12><H4>12</H4></TD><TD><P>And ELOHIYM said unto     
Abraham, Let it not be grievous in thy sight because of the lad, and because of 
thy bondwoman; in all that Sarah hath said unto thee, hearken unto her voice;   
for in Isaac shall thy seed be called.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A       
NAME=V13><H4>13</H4></TD><TD><P>And also of the son of the bondwoman will I     
make a nation, because he is thy seed.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A       
NAME=V14><H4>14</H4></TD><TD><P>And Abraham rose up early in the morning, and   
took bread, and a bottle of water, and gave it unto Hagar, putting it on her    
shoulder, and the child, and sent her away: and she departed, and wandered in   
the wilderness of Beersheba.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V15><H4>   
15</H4></TD><TD><P>And the water was spent in the bottle, and she cast the      
child under one of the shrubs.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V16><H4> 
16</H4></TD><TD><P>And she went, and sat her down over against him a good way   
off, as it were a bow shot: for she said, Let me not see the death of the       
child. And she sat over against him, and lift up her voice, and wept.</P></TD>  
</TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V17><H4>17</H4></TD><TD><P>And ELOHIYM heard    
the voice of the lad; and the angel of ELOHIYM called to Hagar out of heaven,   
and said unto her, What aileth thee, Hagar? fear not; for ELOHIYM hath heard    
the voice of the lad where he is.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V18>  
<H4>18</H4></TD><TD><P>Arise, lift up the lad, and hold him in thine hand; for  
I will make him a great nation.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V19><H4>
19</H4></TD><TD><P>And ELOHIYM opened her eyes, and she saw a well of water;    
and she went, and filled the bottle with water, and gave the lad drink.</P></TD>
</TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V20><H4>20</H4></TD><TD><P>And ELOHIYM was with 
the lad; and he grew, and dwelt in the wilderness, and became an archer.</P>    
</TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V21><H4>21</H4></TD><TD><P>And he dwelt in 
the wilderness of Paran: and his mother took him a wife out of the land of      
Egypt.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V22><H4>22</H4></TD><TD><P>And   
it came to pass at that time, that Abimelech and Phichol the chief captain of   
his host spake unto Abraham, saying, ELOHIYM is with thee in all that thou      
doest:</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V23><H4>23</H4></TD><TD><P>Now   
therefore swear unto me here by ELOHIYM that thou wilt not deal falsely with    
me, nor with my son, nor with my son's son: but according to the kindness that  
I have done unto thee, thou shalt do unto me, and to the land wherein thou hast 
sojourned.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V24><H4>24</H4></TD><TD><P>  
And Abraham said, I will swear.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V25><H4>
25</H4></TD><TD><P>And Abraham reproved Abimelech because of a well of water,   
which Abimelech's servants had violently taken away.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD       
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V26><H4>26</H4></TD><TD><P>And Abimelech said, I wot not who 
hath done this thing; neither didst thou tell me, neither yet heard I of it,    
but to day.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V27><H4>27</H4></TD><TD><P> 
And Abraham took sheep and oxen, and gave them unto Abimelech; and both of them 
made a covenant.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V28><H4>28</H4></TD>   
<TD><P>And Abraham set seven ewe lambs of the flock by themselves.</P></TD></TR>
<TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V29><H4>29</H4></TD><TD><P>And Abimelech said unto   
Abraham, What mean these seven ewe lambs which thou hast set by themselves?</P> 
</TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V30><H4>30</H4></TD><TD><P>And he said,    
For these seven ewe lambs shalt thou take of my hand, that they may be a        
witness unto me, that I have digged this well.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP> 
<A NAME=V31><H4>31</H4></TD><TD><P>Wherefore he called that place Beersheba;    
because there they sware both of them.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A       
NAME=V32><H4>32</H4></TD><TD><P>Thus they made a covenant at Beersheba: then    
Abimelech rose up, and Phichol the chief captain of his host, and they returned 
into the land of the Philistines.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V33>  
<H4>33</H4></TD><TD><P>And Abraham planted a grove in Beersheba, and called     
there on the name of YHVH, the everlasting EL.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP> 
<A NAME=V34><H4>34</H4></TD><TD><P>And Abraham sojourned in the Philistines'    
land many days.</P></TD></TR></TABLE><!--This Software is copyright 2000 by     
